ROSWELL DRAINAGE DISTRICT, a Corporation, Organized and Existing Under and by Virtue of the Laws of the State of New Mexico, v. Gerald PARKER et al. No. 871. Circuit Court of Appeals, Tenth Circuit. Sept. 10, 1934. Charles R. Brice, of Roswell, N. M., for appellant. Ilurd & Crile, of Roswell, N. M., for appellees.

Before LEWIS, McDERMOTT, and BRATTON, Circuit Judges.

PER CURIAM.

Appeal dismissed on stipulation.
